        - Executive Summary, Intro, Conclusion: Formatted text blocks. Goal: Inform. Method: HTML paragraphs, headings. Interaction: None. Justification: Direct presentation of narrative content.
        - Phases (30/60/120 Days): Main sections. Goal: Organize & Inform. Method: Tab navigation (JS). Interaction: Click to switch views. Justification: Clear separation of chronological stages.
        - Strategic Pillars (within Phases - e.g., Performance Marketing, CRO): Sub-sections. Goal: Detail specific strategies. Method: Accordions/Cards (HTML/JS). Interaction: Click to expand/collapse. Justification: Progressive disclosure, reduces cognitive load.
        - Table 1 (Paid Channel Snapshot) & Table 2 (OKRs): Data presentation. Goal: Compare & Inform. Method: HTML tables. Interaction: None (static display). Justification: Structured display of tabular data.
        - Conceptual LTV Comparison: Illustrative chart. Goal: Compare. Method: Chart.js Bar Chart. Interaction: Tooltips. Justification: Visual comparison of LTV types.
        - Blended MER Concept: Diagram. Goal: Explain. Method: HTML/CSS boxes & arrows. Interaction: None. Justification: Visual explanation of a key metric.
        - Creative Testing Framework: Diagram. Goal: Explain process. Method: HTML/CSS flow diagram. Interaction: None. Justification: Visual outline of a process.
        - Unified Reporting Data Flow: Diagram. Goal: Explain process. Method: HTML/CSS block diagram. Interaction: None. Justification: Visualizing data integration.
        - Key Acronyms (ROAS, MER, LTV, etc.): Inform. Method: Tooltips on text (HTML title attribute). Interaction: Hover. Justification: Quick clarification.
        - All textual content directly from the report, condensed for cards/accordions.
        - Library/Method: Chart.js for charts, Vanilla JS for interactions, Tailwind CSS for styling.
        - CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
