                        <h4 class="text-md font-semibold mt-3 mb-2">2. Identifying Top-Performing Creatives & Ad Hooks for Rapid Testing</h4>
                        <p>An in-depth analysis of existing ad creatives across all platforms will be conducted to identify patterns in top-performing assets. This includes a review of ad copy, visuals, and specific "hooks." Immediate testing ideas will be proposed based on these findings, prioritizing high-impact, low-effort changes that align with Higround's unique aesthetic and hype-driven brand identity.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="accordion-item mb-4 border border-slate-300 rounded-lg">
                    <button class="accordion-button w-full flex justify-between items-center text-left p-4 bg-slate-50 hover:bg-slate-200 rounded-t-lg focus:outline-none">
                        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-sky-700">B. Customer Data & Retention Initiatives</h3>
                        <span class="accordion-icon text-sky-700 text-xl">▼</span>
                    </button>
                    <div class="accordion-content bg-white p-4 rounded-b-lg">
                        <p class="mb-3">This area focuses on leveraging customer data from Shopify, Klaviyo, and other EMS for robust segmentation. It also outlines quick-win recommendations for retention flows and winback sequences to enhance customer loyalty and LTV.</p>

                        <h4 class="text-md font-semibold mt-3 mb-2">1. Shopify, Klaviyo, and EMS Data Analysis for Customer Segmentation</h4>
                        <p>A deep dive into customer data will be undertaken to build robust customer segments by consolidating zero-party and first-party data. Key segments to identify include:</p>
                        <ul class="list-disc ml-5 mb-3">
                            <li>Frequent Buyers/Collectors</li>
                            <li>High-Value Customers (HVCs)</li>
                            <li>Drop Enthusiasts</li>
                            <li>Abandoned Cart/Browse Abandoners</li>
                            <li>Inactive/Churn Risk Customers</li>
                            <li>Product-Specific Buyers/IP Loyalists</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>A deeper understanding of collector archetypes (Completionists, IP Loyalists, Aesthetic Collectors, Investment Buyers) will enable hyper-personalized messaging and product recommendations, significantly boosting engagement and LTV.</p>

                        <h4 class="text-md font-semibold mt-3 mb-2">2. Quick Win Retention Flow & Winback Sequence Recommendations</h4>
                        <p>Based on initial data analysis, immediate improvements will be recommended for existing Klaviyo automation workflows. The focus will be on:</p>
                        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 my-4">
                            <div class="quick-win-card p-4 rounded-lg">
                                <h5 class="font-semibold text-amber-700 mb-1">Abandoned Cart Recovery</h5>
                                <p class="text-sm">Optimize flows with personalized messages, urgency, and incentives.</p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="quick-win-card p-4 rounded-lg">
                                <h5 class="font-semibold text-amber-700 mb-1">Post-Purchase Follow-Up</h5>
                                <p class="text-sm">Enhance thank-you emails, prompt reviews, suggest complementary products.</p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="quick-win-card p-4 rounded-lg">
                                <h5 class="font-semibold text-amber-700 mb-1">Welcome Series</h5>
                                <p class="text-sm">Ensure a warm welcome introducing the brand, products, and drop expectations.</p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="quick-win-card p-4 rounded-lg">
                                <h5 class="font-semibold text-amber-700 mb-1">Back-in-Stock Alerts</h5>
                                <p class="text-sm">Implement/optimize notifications for restocked limited drops.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <p>For customers who miss truly limited drops, communication will acknowledge the missed opportunity and redirect interest to future drops or similar editions, transforming a potential negative experience into a lead-generation opportunity.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
