                    <div class="accordion-content bg-white p-4 rounded-b-lg">
                        <p class="mb-3">This involves evaluating current affiliate and influencer campaigns to identify successes, gaps, and scalable opportunities, with a focus on authenticity and alignment with Higround's brand.</p>
                        <h4 class="text-md font-semibold mt-3 mb-2">1. Evaluation of Existing Campaigns: Gaps & Scalable Opportunities</h4>
                        <p>A thorough evaluation of Higround's current affiliate and influencer marketing efforts will be conducted. Focus areas include:</p>
                        <ul class="list-disc ml-5 mb-3">
                            <li><strong>Influencer Quality & Alignment:</strong> Assessing partners for content quality, audience demographics, and genuine alignment with Higround's premium, aesthetic, and gaming culture.</li>
                            <li><strong>Micro-Influencer Potential:</strong> Evaluating the mix for opportunities with micro-influencers who have highly engaged, niche communities.</li>
                            <li><strong><span class="tooltip">UGC<span class="tooltiptext">User-Generated Content</span></span> Pipeline:</strong> Assessing effectiveness in generating high-quality, authentic UGC.</li>
                            <li><strong>Affiliate Models:</strong> Reviewing commission structures, especially for limited drops, to explore time-limited or product-specific commissions.</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>The audit will prioritize influencers and UGC creators demonstrating genuine passion and natural alignment with Higround's aesthetic, emphasizing authenticity as a key driver of trust and conversion.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="accordion-item mb-4 border border-slate-300 rounded-lg">
                    <button class="accordion-button w-full flex justify-between items-center text-left p-4 bg-slate-50 hover:bg-slate-200 rounded-t-lg focus:outline-none">
                        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-sky-700">D. Conversion Rate Optimization (CRO) Accelerators</h3>
                        <span class="accordion-icon text-sky-700 text-xl">▼</span>
                    </button>
                    <div class="accordion-content bg-white p-4 rounded-b-lg">
                        <p class="mb-3">This initiative focuses on rapid <span class="tooltip">CRO<span class="tooltiptext">Conversion Rate Optimization</span></span> improvements for landing pages, checkout UX, and product detail pages to maximize conversions, especially during high-traffic drops.</p>
                        <h4 class="text-md font-semibold mt-3 mb-2">1. Fast-Track CRO Improvements: Landing Pages & Checkout UX</h4>
                        <p>Rapid CRO improvements will be initiated:</p>
                        <ul class="list-disc ml-5 mb-3">
                            <li><strong>Landing Pages:</strong> Streamline for a single goal, ensure message match with ads, A/B test headlines/CTAs.</li>
                            <li><strong>Checkout UX:</strong> Simplify to reduce friction, minimize steps, offer guest checkout, multiple payment options (including BNPL), and optimize for mobile.</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>Given Higround's flash-sale-like drops, CRO must prioritize optimization for extreme pressure and speed, including site speed improvements, mobile-first responsiveness, one-click checkout options, and real-time inventory updates.</p>

                        <h4 class="text-md font-semibold mt-3 mb-2">2. Initial Product Page Optimization for Hype & Scarcity</h4>
                        <p>Product detail pages (PDPs) will be optimized to maximize hype and scarcity:</p>
                        <ul class="list-disc ml-5 mb-3">
                            <li><strong>Clear Scarcity & Urgency Indicators:</strong> Stock counters, countdown timers, scarcity-infused copy.</li>
                            <li><strong>High-Quality Visuals & Storytelling:</strong> High-res images, captivating videos, aspirational content.</li>
                            <li><strong>Social Proof:</strong> Customer reviews, ratings, UGC.</li>
                            <li><strong>Optimized Sold-Out Pages:</strong> Transform sold-out pages into strategic assets by capturing future intent with "notify me for future drops" CTAs.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div id="phase2" class="tab-content bg-white p-6 rounded-b-lg rounded-tr-lg shadow-lg report-text">
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">IV. Phase 2: Days 31–60 – Build & Launch</h2>
                <p>This phase focuses on building out new strategic frameworks and launching initiatives based on the insights gained from the initial deep dive. Key areas include innovating creative strategy, operationalizing growth with OKRs and unified reporting, and deepening customer relationships.</p>

                <div class="accordion-item mb-4 border border-slate-300 rounded-lg">
                    <button class="accordion-button w-full flex justify-between items-center text-left p-4 bg-slate-50 hover:bg-slate-200 rounded-t-lg focus:outline-none">
                        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-sky-700">A. Innovative Creative & Content Strategy</h3>
                        <span class="accordion-icon text-sky-700 text-xl">▼</span>
                    </button>
                    <div class="accordion-content bg-white p-4 rounded-b-lg">
                        <p class="mb-3">Here, the focus shifts to launching a direct response creative testing framework tailored for limited drops and scaling the affiliate/influencer pipeline with authentic UGC creators.</p>
                        <h4 class="text-md font-semibold mt-3 mb-2">1. Launching a Direct Response Creative Testing Framework for Limited Drops</h4>
                        <p>A robust, continuous creative testing framework will be launched to combat ad fatigue and maximize conversions for limited drops. Steps include:</p>
                        <ul class="list-disc ml-5 mb-3">
                            <li><strong>Strategic Planning:</strong> Define clear objectives for each test.</li>
                            <li><strong>High-Velocity Creative Development:</strong> Pipeline for 3-5 new variations per drop, leveraging AI tools and diverse ad hooks.</li>
                            <li><strong>Systematic Testing Methodology:</strong> Rigorous A/B and multivariate testing.</li>
                            <li><strong>Data-Driven Analysis & Optimization:</strong> Evaluate performance and capture learnings.</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>The framework will test creatives emphasizing performance benefits versus aesthetic/lifestyle appeal to understand what resonates with different audience segments for various product lines.</p>
                        <div class="my-4 p-3 border border-sky-300 rounded-lg bg-sky-50">
                            <h5 class="font-semibold text-sky-700 mb-2">Conceptual: Creative Testing Flow</h5>
                            <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row items-center justify-around text-sm">
                                <div class="diagram-box">Define Objectives</div>
                                <div class="diagram-arrow hidden md:flex">&rarr;</div> <div class="diagram-arrow flex md:hidden">&darr;</div>
                                <div class="diagram-box">Develop Variations (3-5)</div>
                                <div class="diagram-arrow hidden md:flex">&rarr;</div> <div class="diagram-arrow flex md:hidden">&darr;</div>
                                <div class="diagram-box">A/B Test Systematically</div>
                                <div class="diagram-arrow hidden md:flex">&rarr;</div> <div class="diagram-arrow flex md:hidden">&darr;</div>
                                <div class="diagram-box">Analyze & Optimize</div>
                                <div class="diagram-arrow hidden md:flex">&rarr;</div> <div class="diagram-arrow flex md:hidden">&darr;</div>
                                <div class="diagram-box">Iterate</div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <h4 class="text-md font-semibold mt-3 mb-2">2. Scaling Affiliate/Influencer Pipeline with Authentic UGC Creators</h4>
                        <p>Affiliate and influencer efforts will be scaled with an emphasis on authentic UGC creators. Strategy includes:</p>
                        <ul class="list-disc ml-5 mb-3">
                            <li><strong>Smarter Negotiation & Usage Rights:</strong> Secure broad usage rights for UGC.</li>
                            <li><strong>Creator Tiers & Niche Focus:</strong> Blend nano, micro, and mid-tier influencers with niche passion.</li>
                            <li><strong>Structured & Empowering Briefs:</strong> Clear guidance allowing authentic voice.</li>
                            <li><strong>Diverse Content Types:</strong> Unboxings, reviews, usage scenarios.</li>
                            <li><strong>Strategic Incentives:</strong> Early access, exclusive webinars, recognition.</li>
                            <li><strong>Pipeline Management Tools:</strong> Implement tools like Modash or Grin.</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>UGC will be leveraged pre-drop for hype (sneak peeks) and post-launch for validation (unboxing, setups), transforming UGC into a full-funnel content strategy.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="accordion-item mb-4 border border-slate-300 rounded-lg">
                    <button class="accordion-button w-full flex justify-between items-center text-left p-4 bg-slate-50 hover:bg-slate-200 rounded-t-lg focus:outline-none">
                        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-sky-700">B. Operationalizing Growth: OKRs & Unified Reporting</h3>
                        <span class="accordion-icon text-sky-700 text-xl">▼</span>
                    </button>
                    <div class="accordion-content bg-white p-4 rounded-b-lg">
                        <p class="mb-3">This section details the implementation of <span class="tooltip">OKRs<span class="tooltiptext">Objectives and Key Results</span></span> for strategic alignment and the rollout of new dashboards and reporting flows for unified, real-time insights.</p>
                        <h4 class="text-md font-semibold mt-3 mb-2">1. Implementing OKRs Across Paid, Influencer, and CRO Initiatives</h4>
                        <p>Objectives and Key Results (OKRs) will be implemented across paid acquisition, influencer/UGC marketing, and CRO to ensure strategic alignment and measurable progress. Objectives will be qualitative and aspirational, while Key Results will be quantitative and verifiable. OKRs will balance immediate "drop success" with long-term "brand health."</p>
                        
                        <h4 class="text-md font-semibold mt-4 mb-2">Table 2: Growth Marketing OKRs (Days 31-60)</h4>
                        <div class="table-container my-4">
                            <table class="min-w-full">
                                <thead>
                                    <tr>
                                        <th>Pillar</th>
                                        <th>Objective</th>
                                        <th>Key Results (3-5 per objective)</th>
                                        <th>Measurement</th>
                                    </tr>
                                </thead>
                                <tbody>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td><strong>Paid Acquisition</strong></td>
                                        <td>Optimize Paid Channels for Drop Profitability</td>
                                        <td>Increase blended ROAS to X.X for all new drops launched in period. Reduce Cost Per Acquisition (CAC) by Y% for new drop buyers. Achieve Z% increase in qualified traffic from paid channels.</td>
                                        <td>GA4, Meta Ads Dashboard, TikTok Ads Dashboard, Google Ads Dashboard</td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td><strong>Influencer/UGC Marketing</strong></td>
                                        <td>Amplify Authentic Hype Through Community Creators</td>
                                        <td>Achieve Y% increase in qualified UGC volume from micro-influencers. Increase engagement rate on influencer-driven content by Z%. Drive X% of new drop sign-ups via influencer channels.</td>
                                        <td>Influencer Platform Analytics, Social Media Analytics, Klaviyo</td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td><strong>Conversion Rate Optimization (CRO)</strong></td>
                                        <td>Streamline User Journey for Peak Conversion</td>
                                        <td>Reduce checkout abandonment rate by Z%. Increase average order value (AOV) by W% for drop purchases. Improve product page conversion rate by V%.</td>
                                        <td>Shopify Analytics, GA4, Heatmaps/Session Recordings</td>
                                    </tr>
                                </tbody>
                            </table>
                        </div>

                        <h4 class="text-md font-semibold mt-3 mb-2">2. Rolling Out New Dashboards & Reporting Flows (Shopify, Ad Platforms, Klaviyo, GA4 Integration)</h4>
                        <p>A unified reporting infrastructure will be established by integrating data from Shopify, ad platforms, and Klaviyo into centralized dashboards, with GA4 as the analytical backbone. Process includes:</p>
                        <ul class="list-disc ml-5 mb-3">
                            <li><strong><span class="tooltip">ETL<span class="tooltiptext">Extract, Transform, Load</span></span> Process:</strong> Automate data pulling, cleaning, and loading.</li>
                            <li><strong>Centralized Visualization:</strong> Custom dashboards (e.g., Looker Studio) for a unified view.</li>
                            <li><strong>Key Metrics for Drop Analysis:</strong> Track <span class="tooltip">KPIs<span class="tooltiptext">Key Performance Indicators</span></span> like conversion rate, AOV, LTV, sales growth.</li>
                            <li><strong>Custom GA4 Reports:</strong> Deeper insights into product performance and user funnels.</li>
                            <li><strong>Klaviyo Product Analysis Dashboard:</strong> Insights for cross-sell/next-purchase.</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>The dashboard will prominently feature "Blended MER" (Total Revenue / Total Marketing Spend) for each drop period, providing a holistic view of marketing efficiency.</p>
                        <div class="my-4 p-3 border border-sky-300 rounded-lg bg-sky-50">
                            <h5 class="font-semibold text-sky-700 mb-2">Conceptual: Unified Reporting Data Flow</h5>
