            <div id="phase3" class="tab-content bg-white p-6 rounded-b-lg rounded-tr-lg shadow-lg report-text">
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">V. Phase 3: Days 61–120 – Scale & Optimize</h2>
                <p>The final phase focuses on aggressively scaling successful initiatives, continuous optimization of strategies, and fostering deep cross-functional collaboration to drive sustained, long-term growth for Higround.</p>

                <div class="accordion-item mb-4 border border-slate-300 rounded-lg">
                    <button class="accordion-button w-full flex justify-between items-center text-left p-4 bg-slate-50 hover:bg-slate-200 rounded-t-lg focus:outline-none">
                        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-sky-700">A. Aggressive Scaling & Performance Maximization</h3>
                        <span class="accordion-icon text-sky-700 text-xl">▼</span>
                    </button>
                    <div class="accordion-content bg-white p-4 rounded-b-lg">
                        <p class="mb-3">This involves scaling the best-performing ad creatives and influencer partnerships to maximize LTV and new customer acquisition, alongside launching targeted micro-campaigns for upcoming drops.</p>
                        <h4 class="text-md font-semibold mt-3 mb-2">1. Scaling Best-Performing Ad Creatives & Influencers to Maximize LTV & New Customer Acquisition</h4>
                        <p>Effective ad creatives and influencer partnerships will be scaled:</p>
                        <ul class="list-disc ml-5 mb-3">
                            <li><strong>Paid Media Scaling:</strong> Increase budget for winning ad sets, explore new placements, leverage lookalike audiences based on high-LTV segments, transition to LTV-based bidding.</li>
                            <li><strong>Influencer & UGC Scaling:</strong> Increase investment in high-performing creators, expand the network with niche micro-influencers, repurpose UGC across channels.</li>
                        </ul>

                        <h4 class="text-md font-semibold mt-3 mb-2">2. Launching Micro-Campaigns Aligned with Upcoming Drops & Partnerships</h4>
                        <p>Strategic micro-campaigns will be launched for upcoming drops:</p>
                        <ul class="list-disc ml-5 mb-3">
                            <li><strong>Pre-Launch Hype Generation:</strong> Teaser campaigns, cryptic visuals, countdowns, exclusive sneak peeks for VIPs.</li>
                            <li><strong>Drop-Specific Messaging:</strong> Highlight unique themes, designs, and partners; emphasize limited availability.</li>
                            <li><strong>Targeted Channel Activation:</strong> Allocate budget based on the drop's target audience.</li>
                            <li><strong>Post-Drop Follow-Up:</strong> Thank purchasers, encourage UGC, re-engage those who missed out.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="accordion-item mb-4 border border-slate-300 rounded-lg">
                    <button class="accordion-button w-full flex justify-between items-center text-left p-4 bg-slate-50 hover:bg-slate-200 rounded-t-lg focus:outline-none">
                        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-sky-700">B. Strategic CRO Roadmap & Product Enhancement</h3>
                        <span class="accordion-icon text-sky-700 text-xl">▼</span>
                    </button>
                    <div class="accordion-content bg-white p-4 rounded-b-lg">
                        <p class="mb-3">A continuous CRO testing roadmap will be established for iterative improvements across landing pages, product details, bundling strategies, and the checkout flow, with a constant focus on site speed and technical UX.</p>
                        <h4 class="text-md font-semibold mt-3 mb-2">1. Leading CRO Testing Roadmap (New Landing Pages, Product Detail Tweaks, Bundling Tests)</h4>
                        <p>A continuous CRO testing roadmap will be led:</p>
                        <ul class="list-disc ml-5 mb-3">
                            <li><strong>Landing Page Optimization:</strong> A/B test new layouts, value propositions, CTAs for drops and evergreen lines.</li>
                            <li><strong>PDP Enhancements:</strong> Test placement of info, scarcity tactics, interactive elements (360 views, videos).</li>
                            <li><strong>Bundling & Upsell/Cross-sell Tests:</strong> A/B test product bundles and post-purchase offers to increase AOV.</li>
                            <li><strong>Checkout Flow Refinements:</strong> Continuously optimize based on analytics and user behavior.</li>
                            <li><strong>Site Speed & Technical UX:</strong> Prioritize ongoing site speed optimization, especially for mobile.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="accordion-item mb-4 border border-slate-300 rounded-lg">
